On Mother’s Day, eNCA gets an insight from some of the women in politics how they plan to relax and enjoy this day dedicated to them. eNCA's Tshegohaco Moagi reports. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA – With the 2019 election done and dusted, women in politics can take a break and relax with their families on Mother’s Day. It has been a hectic couple of months for politicians including the ladies in this male-dominated arena. READ: Fun behind the scenes as an IEC worker On On Mother’s Day, eNCA gets an insight from some of the women in politics how they plan to relax and enjoy this day dedicated to them. eNCA reporter Tshegohaco Moagi has more details in the video above.